definition: Nasr or Nasser (Arab name)/Gamal Abdel Nasser (1918-1970), Egyptian President
to receive/to accept/to enjoy/to bring into/to pay (tax etc)/nano- (one billionth)/to reinforce sole of shoes or stockings by close sewing
to compete/competition/match/to surpass/better than/superior to/to excel

sentences.english: In fact, Mr Nasser does most of the chatting.
sentences.chinese: 實際上，多數情況都是納賽爾先生在聊天。

sentences.english: What caused Nasser to bark and run to the road?
sentences.chinese: 納賽爾爲什麼要狂叫並且還要跑到路上？

sentences.english: After the death of Nasser, Sadat successfully become the third president of Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 納賽爾逝世後，薩達特順利成爲埃及第三任總統。
